There is no law in Japan that specifically addresses cookies, but it is generally considered that cookies fall under the definition of the Personally Referable Information and thus the transfer of such data would be regulated by the APPI in certain circumstances. In addition, if the information obtained through cookies may identify a certain individual in conjunction with other easily-referenced information (eg member registration) and it is utilized (eg for marketing purposes), such Purpose of Use of information obtained through the use of cookies must be disclosed under the APPI.Last modified 1 Jan 2022
				
			